The paper describes a computational model of social norms that can be used to create social simulations, explain or predict human behavior, and as a component of robots or agents that need to interact with humans in specific social-cultural settings. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) which deals with intelligent agents and their behavior, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) which deals with social interactions and networks, cs.CY (Computers and Society) which deals with the impact of computing on society, cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) which deals with social and behavioral aspects of computing, and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) which deals with the design and evaluation of interactive systems.
